    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-02-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-02-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="52" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Kimberly</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States in Central America</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-02-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 23, 1891</hi>.</date>
                            (Received March 13.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 253.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Respectfully referring to my No. 239, of
                        January 28, I have the honor to inclose herewith a letter addressed to me by
                        Consul Peterson, at Tegucigalpa, Honduras, bearing upon the subject
                        mentioned in my above-named number.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Samuel Kimberly</hi>.<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Chargé d’Affaires ad int</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
